// Plan 118.5 V3 Ф.2 NEG T5 — `ro mut T` inside a nested (Array) constructor
// → error (no binding context for disambiguation).
//
// Per D216 V3 §V3.1: при nested constructor position (Array, etc.), no
// binding context — the ro+mut combination is invalid regardless of T's
// storage class.
//
// NOTE (Plan 147 / D246 migration): the original form used a *pointer*
// constructor (`* ro mut Acc`). Under the 3-axis canon a bare `*T ≡ *ro T`,
// so an explicit `*ro` is a HARD ERROR E_REDUNDANT_POINTER_RO fired at parse
// time — it would mask this §V3.1 ro+mut value-type conflict. The conflict is
// preserved here in an `[]ro mut Acc` array constructor, which is the same
// «nested constructor, no binding context» position without the `*ro` clash.
//
// EXPECT_COMPILE_ERROR E_MUTABILITY_CONFLICT_VALUE_TYPE

module neg.t5_neg_ro_mut_nested_constructor

type Acc {
    id i64
}

extern "nova" fn p(x []ro mut Acc) -> ()
